====Verb====
{{en-verb|es}}

# {{label|en|transitive}} To strike with a lash; to whip or scourge with a lash, or with something like one.
#: ''We lash the pupil, and defraud the ward.'' &mdash; [[w:John Dryden|John Dryden]]
# {{label|en|transitive}} To strike forcibly and quickly, as with a lash; to beat, or beat upon, with a motion like that of a lash.
#: ''the whale lashes the sea with its tail.''
#: ''And big waves lash the frighted shores.'' &mdash; [[w:John Dryden|John Dryden]]
#* {{quote-journal
|date=December 29, 2010
|author=Chris Whyatt
|title=Chelsea 1 - 0 Bolton
|work=BBC
|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/9309542.stm
|page=
|passage=Carlo Ancelotti's out-of-sorts team struggled to hit the target in the first half as Bolton threatened with Matthew Taylor '''lashing''' just wide.}}
# {{label|en|transitive}} To throw out with a jerk or quickly.
#: ''He falls, and lashing up his heels, his rider throws.'' &mdash; [[w:John Dryden|John Dryden]]
# {{label|en|transitive}} To scold; to berate; to satirize; to censure with severity.
#: ''to lash vice''
# {{label|en|intransitive}} To ply the whip; to strike.
# {{label|en|intransitive}} To utter censure or sarcastic language.
#: ''To laugh at follies, or to lash at vice.'' &mdash; [[w:John Dryden|John Dryden]]
# {{label|en|intransitive|of rain}} To fall heavily, especially in the phrase ''[[lash down]]''
#* {{quote-journal
|date=October 1, 2011
|author=Tom Fordyce
|title=Rugby World Cup 2011: England 16-12 Scotland
|work=BBC Sport
|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_union/15124512.stm
|page=
|passage=With rain '''lashing''' across the ground at kick-off and every man in Auckland seemingly either English-born or supporting Scotland, Eden Park was transformed into Murrayfield in March.}}

